Jawk: AWK for Java
==================

<!-- MACRO{toc|fromDepth=2|toDepth=3|id=toc} -->

Overview
--------

Jawk is a pure Java implementation of [AWK](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/AWK). You can run AWK programs in a JVM
application and integrate with your Java code:

> [!TABS]
> - CLI
>
>   ```shell-session
>   $ echo "hello world" | java -jar jawk-${project.version}-standalone.jar '{ print $2 ", " $1 "!" }'
>   world, hello!
>   ```
>
> - Java
>
>   ```java
>   Awk awk = new Awk();
>   String result = awk.script("{ print toupper($0) }").input("hello world").execute();
>   // result = "HELLO WORLD\n"
>   ```

